  "why": "The paper describes applying gradient-based, in-memory perturbations to image inputs (entropy-guided mutator maximizing LIB and FOL) and uses perceptual filtering (SSIM) to retain visually similar seeds, but it contains no statements that mutations are clipped/rounded or otherwise constrained to match serialized input formats (e.g., integer [0,255] pixels) or that mutated inputs are validated to survive disk serialization. The mutation description emphasizes floating-point gradient steps and randomized step sizes without any mention of enforcing format constraints or serialization-aware postprocessing; thus fault-inducing perturbations introduced in memory could be lost or altered when saved/serialized, and the paper does not explicitly address this reproducibility issue.",
